    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_281335050" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/281335050" />
    <a title="aPriL does feral sometimes " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3409532-april-does-feral-sometimes"><img alt="aPriL does feral sometimes " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1478243665p2/3409532.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/281335050?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="aPriL does feral sometimes " class="user" itemprop="url" name="aPriL does feral sometimes " href="/user/show/3409532-april-does-feral-sometimes">aPriL does feral sometimes </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3409532-april-does-feral-sometimes?shelf=unbearably-sad">unbearably-sad</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3409532-april-does-feral-sometimes?shelf=literary">literary</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer281335050" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14638871251612616313">The extremely wretched existence of an Afghanistan woman along with the sick and rotten life that Afghan men have created for everyone in that damned country is revealed by this surprising high-art novella. All of the story’s action occurs in a single room so this book could easily be turned into a play. It is a frank, honest perfect-for-a-stage-monologue. <br/><br/>The woman’s recital reveals a country that hides its barnyard mentality and psychopathic cruelty behind twisted interpretations of an already</span>
  <span id="freeText14638871251612616313" style="display:none">The extremely wretched existence of an Afghanistan woman along with the sick and rotten life that Afghan men have created for everyone in that damned country is revealed by this surprising high-art novella. All of the story’s action occurs in a single room so this book could easily be turned into a play. It is a frank, honest perfect-for-a-stage-monologue. <br /><br />The woman’s recital reveals a country that hides its barnyard mentality and psychopathic cruelty behind twisted interpretations of an already illogical collection of religious instructions. As peculiar as the Torah, the Bible and the Quran can read to those who bother to study them, what the Afghans have done with the Quran, a book written in the eighth-century, consisting of third-hand translated stories of Babylonian folk tales and ridiculous body-function rituals that HAD to be created by someone with autism or obsessive-compulsive disorder, is criminal. <br /><br />It is amazing such a sick and maimed society is often discussed as if in the interests of fairness we must pretend it is sane and legitimate, with normal governing principles grounding the daily lives of all the followers of extreme Islam. For God's sake, the average male life expectancy in Afghanistan is around 40, women are basically treated like they are breeding dogs, children are disposable slaves and the men are knuckle-dragging mouth-breathers. <br /><br />Perhaps after two (and still counting down) decades of modern war Afghans will have to return to living in caves trying to remember how to make a fire. No one wants to say out loud how insane this country is. Everyone knows it, the same way we all knew how sick Khmer Cambodia, North Korea, Nazi Germany, Stalin's Russia, Idi Amin' s Uganda, and the current Somalia, is. It is similar to being respectful and politically correct about a rabies-infected bat actively attacking and biting you. <br /><br />If only people would discuss more often and openly how much opium has infiltrated all aspects of Afghan society. And since Afghan men demonize women the men have turned to slaved impoverished 'boy dancers' which is creating a future generation of sick, damaged men. The worst part is how Pakistan and Iran are cynically and malignantly 'helping' Afghanistan turn Afghans into Neanderthal primitives to keep their home populations distracted by using Afghans as political catspaws (a role the Palestinians know very well), while China quietly steals every valuable mineral resource Afghanistan possesses, screaming that their intervention is stopping the USA from doing so. <br /><br />It's all so disgusting. And hopeless. In my opinion, Afghanistan is suffering an out of control forest fire of fundamentalist religion that will burn until all of the land is destroyed. Since no one can help, we should leave them alone to their devolution and read books like this one as cautionary tales.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14638871251612616313" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


