  <span id="freeText564788865645725631" style="display:none">1/5<br /><br />I probably read enough about Afghanistan -for now- through Khaled Hosseini to find The Patience Stone dull. Couldn’t connect with the nameless woman and truthfully I was just waiting patiently for her to strangle her husband with the prayer beads throughout the novel. <br />*<br />Afghanistan is a sad country with a sadder history, Rahimi didn’t bring anything new to the table. I pray that no one ends up having this short novel as their introduction to Afghanistan as a country or a culture. <br /><br /><br />— <br />The beginning was interesting but I guess that was it. Also the fly scene was disgusting. <br /><br /><br />—— <br /><br />I might add more stuff later.</span>
