<div id="review_3531196248" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3531196248" />
    <a title="Souvik Barik" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/91198809-souvik-barik"><img alt="Souvik Barik" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1644079069p2/91198809.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3531196248?book_show_action=true">Sep 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Souvik Barik" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Souvik Barik" href="/user/show/91198809-souvik-barik">Souvik Barik</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099539544" href="/book/show/12194019-the-patience-stone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3531196248" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4515586766185817824">The Patience Stone is a contemplative novella about a woman sitting by her dying husband&apos;s bedside, set in a war-stricken Afghan neighborhood. Rahimi&apos;s unique style of adorning his meticulous narration with occasional terse dialogues produces a tone somewhat resembling the cadaverous husband, with his skeleton sticking out of his withered flesh. The narrator stays in the shadows, while all the characters are anonymous. Owing to it&apos;s simplicity, the narration is laid bare of distractive opulence,</span>
  <span id="freeText4515586766185817824" style="display:none">The Patience Stone is a contemplative novella about a woman sitting by her dying husband's bedside, set in a war-stricken Afghan neighborhood. Rahimi's unique style of adorning his meticulous narration with occasional terse dialogues produces a tone somewhat resembling the cadaverous husband, with his skeleton sticking out of his withered flesh. The narrator stays in the shadows, while all the characters are anonymous. Owing to it's simplicity, the narration is laid bare of distractive opulence, wherein Rahimi's simplistic literary style paints the surroundings and emotions in strokes of visions and sounds, leaving a vivid picture upon the canvas of his readers' mind. Without actually stepping out of the ruined house, readers are able to perceive the bombing and firing of bullets and sharpnels through cries and outbursts, while the woman silently tells her beads and mumbles prayers for her husband's recovery. Juxtaposed against this is the element of melancholic suffering and perpetual torture that this Afghan woman had to endure all throughout her life. Rahimi vents out through the woman's voice the dormant whirlpool of anguish and revenge, as she confronts her husband on his deathbead with condescending truths and subtly mocks him, when he no longer has the obstinacy to rule over her, but to listen with sightless eyes and gasps of dying breath. The title is aptly justified as the man becomes his wife's 'Patience Stone', absorbing all that she has to convey, without bursting or complaining. The story is concluded in an anti-climax, as the behemoth of worldly forces, Fate, takes control and leads these intertwined souls into an abyss of eternal disillusion. Atiq Rahimi has proved his literary mastery and deserves a million stars for this ruminative composition.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4515586766185817824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

