<div id="review_2240304967" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2240304967" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6866817-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1545738352p2/6866817.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2240304967?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/6866817-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2240304967" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2674173280534010920">For my full review, visit: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://amygetslit.com/rtw-afghanistan-the-patience-stone-by-atiq-rahimi/'>http://amygetslit.com/rtw-afghanistan...</a><br/><br/>I am still trying to recover from reading this book. There are so many different themes and layers that are universal in this book, even though the book takes place between a couple in Afghanistan living in one room as a fight between factions carries on outside. Love, sacrifice, silence, war, peace, secrets, salvation, family, motherhood, abandonment. This book touches on all of those themes while telling the story of one woman </span>
  <span id="freeText2674173280534010920" style="display:none">For my full review, visit: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://amygetslit.com/rtw-afghanistan-the-patience-stone-by-atiq-rahimi/">http://amygetslit.com/rtw-afghanistan...</a><br /><br />I am still trying to recover from reading this book. There are so many different themes and layers that are universal in this book, even though the book takes place between a couple in Afghanistan living in one room as a fight between factions carries on outside. Love, sacrifice, silence, war, peace, secrets, salvation, family, motherhood, abandonment. This book touches on all of those themes while telling the story of one woman confessing her secrets to her injured husband as the power dynamic within their marriage shifts. She becomes the one that has power and he is the one that is forced to remain silent and listen to and take in everything she does and has to say. <br /><br />I highly recommend this read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2674173280534010920" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


