<div id="review_1618937168" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1618937168" />
    <a title="Krishna Sruthi Srivalsan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3504721-krishna-sruthi-srivalsan"><img alt="Krishna Sruthi Srivalsan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1425785903p2/3504721.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1618937168?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Krishna Sruthi Srivalsan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Krishna Sruthi Srivalsan" href="/user/show/3504721-krishna-sruthi-srivalsan">Krishna Sruthi Srivalsan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1618937168" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10816086556591799729">According to an old Persian tale, there is a black stone that will listen to all your secrets, all the burdens you have been carrying. It is the patience stone. <i> sang -e-sabur </i> <br/>And then one day when it finally runs out of patience, it will explode. That day, your conscience will be set free.<br/>A woman in a war torn country sits in a room, nursing her comatose husband, and she remembers this story. As she tells the beads on her rosary, she gathers courage to talk about her secrets, which could never</span>
  <span id="freeText10816086556591799729" style="display:none">According to an old Persian tale, there is a black stone that will listen to all your secrets, all the burdens you have been carrying. It is the patience stone. <i> sang -e-sabur </i> <br />And then one day when it finally runs out of patience, it will explode. That day, your conscience will be set free.<br />A woman in a war torn country sits in a room, nursing her comatose husband, and she remembers this story. As she tells the beads on her rosary, she gathers courage to talk about her secrets, which could never been done had her husband been alive. He becomes her patience stone, and some devastating secrets are revealed.<br />Easily the most depressing novel (deceptively simple, it is) I've read till date. And yet, so compelling. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10816086556591799729" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


